	id="Expla_RowColumnSpace">
	<title>Row / Column Space - Explanation</title>
	<sub.page.body>
		<block>
			<para>An element of the row space of the <latex>(m,n)</latex>-matrix <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is of the form</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\Vect{x}</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>s_1R_1+\cdots + s_mR_m</right>
			</computation>
			<para>Each row of <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is a vector in <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>. Therefore the row space of <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is a subvector space of <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>.</para>
		</block>
		
		
		<block>
			<para>An element of the column space of <latex>(m,n)</latex>-matrix <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is of the form</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\Vect{y}</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>t_1C_1+\cdots + t_nC_n</right>
			</computation>
			<para>Each column of <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is a vector in <latex>\RNr[m]</latex>. Therefore the column space of <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is a subvector space of <latex>\RNr[m]</latex>.</para>
		</block>
	</sub.page.body>
</sub.page>